23/07/2004
BIJELJINA, Bosnia and Herzegovina, (BiH) -- SFOR personnel have apprehended a man said to be one of the closest wartime associates of former Bosnian Serb military leader Ratko Mladic.
Fena news agency reports that Rajko Banduka was arrested early Friday (23 July) at his house in Bijeljina, Republika Srpska.
The local police had not been informed of SFOR's operation in advance.
(Fena - 23/07/04)
